Yes. You know my great-great-grandfather and mother was the first Jehovah's Witnesses in my family,

00:25:35.710 --> 00:25:39.710
and here you can see them in 1940s in Ukraine.

00:25:39.710 --> 00:25:44.710
Well, that is definitely a wonderful heritage to be a part of.

00:25:44.710 --> 00:25:55.710
Would you say, Anjel, that the choices that members of your family made over the years had a direct bearing on your being here attending the 149th Class of Gilead?

00:25:55.710 --> 00:26:01.710
Definitely, yes. You know, they were serving Jehovah for many, many years.

00:26:01.710 --> 00:26:07.710
They had very hard but interesting life, life full of many different stories.

00:26:07.710 --> 00:26:14.710
For example, when my great-grandfather was exiled to Siberia because of being a Jehovah's Witness,

00:26:14.710 --> 00:26:22.710
and my great-grandmother would send him magazines hidden in the bottles of pork fat.

00:26:22.710 --> 00:26:24.710
You said pork fat.

00:26:24.710 --> 00:26:27.710
Okay, and that sounds pretty interesting.

00:26:27.710 --> 00:26:33.710
Can you tell us more about this secret pork fat recipe of your great-grandmother?

00:26:33.710 --> 00:26:40.710
Okay, so my mom, she made some photos and sent it to me to explain how it was done.

00:26:40.710 --> 00:26:47.710
So as you can see here, first this fat was melted so that you could have a liquid fat.

00:26:47.710 --> 00:26:52.710
Then you need to wait so that this fat would become hard and thick.

00:26:52.710 --> 00:26:58.710
Then a magazine was wrapped in the linen and hold was made in the fat.

00:26:58.710 --> 00:27:07.710
And then this wrapped magazine was put in the hole and the more fat was put on the top to hide this magazine.

00:27:07.710 --> 00:27:13.710
And now it's done. Now you have both physical and spiritual food in one bottle.

00:27:13.710 --> 00:27:18.710
Well, there it is. Everything you need to survive in Siberia, right?

00:27:18.710 --> 00:27:25.710
Well, let me ask you, did the guards in Siberia ever find those magazines hidden in pork fat?

00:27:25.710 --> 00:27:27.710
Sadly, but yes.

00:27:27.710 --> 00:27:35.710
And that's why they added additional five and a half years for my great-grandfather exiled time in Siberia.

00:27:35.710 --> 00:27:40.710
But soon his son, my grandfather, was exiled to Siberia too.

00:27:40.710 --> 00:27:47.710
And here you can see my great-grandfather on the left and my grandfather on the right.

00:27:47.710 --> 00:27:51.710
When you shared with us some details about your great-grandfather,

00:27:51.710 --> 00:27:55.710
what can you tell us about your grandfather depicted on the right?

00:27:55.710 --> 00:27:59.710
You know, he was so zealous for Jehovah.

00:27:59.710 --> 00:28:05.710
While in Siberia, he was helping in supplying by the literature for local brothers and sisters,

00:28:05.710 --> 00:28:08.710
though it was not always safe to do it.

00:28:08.710 --> 00:28:12.710
Well, clearly they were both courageous men.

00:28:12.710 --> 00:28:18.710
When were your family members allowed to leave Siberia and return to the Ukraine?

00:28:18.710 --> 00:28:21.710
It was in 1967-68.

00:28:21.710 --> 00:28:31.710
And it was then when my great-grandfather started to reproduce Bible magazines and books and whole family helped.

00:28:31.710 --> 00:28:38.710
That's amazing. Were there any particular methods that they used to accomplish this?

00:28:38.710 --> 00:28:44.710
They used several different methods. For example, they used special photo machines, like you see here,

00:28:44.710 --> 00:28:47.710
to make photos of magazines.

00:28:47.710 --> 00:28:55.710
This and similar to these machines were used to make, so to say, handmade literature.

00:28:55.710 --> 00:29:03.710
Well, just looking at those photos, we can see that the men in your family were both courageous and zealous.

00:29:03.710 --> 00:29:07.710
Yes, they were. But so were the women in our family.

00:29:07.710 --> 00:29:13.710
Here, on this photo, you can see my great-grandmother with her daughter.

00:29:13.710 --> 00:29:18.710
And it was her who sent these magazines hidden in the bottles of pork fat.

00:29:18.710 --> 00:29:24.710
And here you can see my grand-mother on my mother's side. She was witnessed too.

00:29:24.710 --> 00:29:28.710
And here you can see her with her children.

00:29:28.710 --> 00:29:33.710
And this little girl with a guitar is my mom.

00:29:33.710 --> 00:29:43.710
And you know, once a government wanted to separate them, they wanted to have public hearing to take all her children away.

00:29:43.710 --> 00:29:53.710
Why they wanted to do it? Because it was then when in Soviet Union, all children were forced to support political ideas of the government.

00:29:53.710 --> 00:29:57.710
But my grand-mother's children choose not to do it.

00:29:58.710 --> 00:30:03.710
That's interesting. The children made this choice. But what about your grand-mother?

00:30:03.710 --> 00:30:12.710
When she's forced to make this choice between what the Communist Party was dictating and what Jehovah says, what does she do?

00:30:12.710 --> 00:30:17.710
She wanted to prove and to show that she was a good mother.

00:30:17.710 --> 00:30:23.710
And she was a good mother because she was Jehovah's Witness, because she believed in God.

00:30:23.710 --> 00:30:30.710
And you know, even during this hearing, one woman stand up and screamed, don't listen to her.

00:30:30.710 --> 00:30:38.710
As you will become Jehovah's Witness too. But people said, no, we want to hear more. So she kept going.

00:30:38.710 --> 00:30:46.710
And when she finished, all people voted in her favor. And she had kept all her children with her.

00:30:47.710 --> 00:30:55.710
And here you can see my grand-mother years later with her family, children, and grandchildren.

00:30:55.710 --> 00:31:04.710
That is an absolutely incredible story. Obviously, Jehovah blessed her for her loyal efforts there.

00:31:04.710 --> 00:31:14.710
But now, Angel, as you reflect upon the decisions that members of your family have made, how have their decisions affected you?

00:31:15.710 --> 00:31:24.710
You know, they helped me to love Jehovah with all my heart and to put him always first in my life.

00:31:24.710 --> 00:31:28.710
Can you provide us an example of that?

00:31:28.710 --> 00:31:38.710
Yes. For example, in Ukraine, all young men are required to do military service. But I, like many other brothers, choose not to do it.

00:31:38.710 --> 00:31:48.710
I choose civilian or alternative service instead. So I was still living at home, but government gives you any work they want.

00:31:48.710 --> 00:31:51.710
And you need to do it for two years.

00:31:51.710 --> 00:31:56.710
If you don't mind my asking, what job did they give you?

00:31:56.710 --> 00:32:02.710
So, okay, they sent me to clean sewer and water system.

00:32:02.710 --> 00:32:09.710
So I need to go inside these tanks, which were so filthy, and I need to clean them out.

00:32:09.710 --> 00:32:17.710
And for me, it was really, very hard work. And sometimes I felt very sad about my situation.

00:32:18.710 --> 00:32:27.710
Yeah, we're so sorry, Angel, that you had to go through that. But we certainly appreciate your loyalty to Jehovah at the same time.

00:32:27.710 --> 00:32:32.710
What helped you to get through that difficult period in your life?

00:32:32.710 --> 00:32:41.710
For me, it was my family. I would think about my grandfather, grandmother, great-grandfather and mother.

00:32:41.710 --> 00:32:48.710
And I thought, they showed me how to do it. They showed me how to go through it.

00:32:48.710 --> 00:32:53.710
They showed me that with Jehovah's help, I can do it.

00:32:53.710 --> 00:32:59.710
Well, you have learned some very powerful lessons from your family.

00:32:59.710 --> 00:33:10.710
And now, here you are at Gilead. You've completed your Gilead training, and we can only imagine how proud and happy your family must be for you.

00:33:10.710 --> 00:33:17.710
Can you tell us what has been the highlight for you, from your Gilead training?

00:33:17.710 --> 00:33:34.710
Yes, Gilead had helped me to see more, to understand more, and to feel more, to see more this wonderful history of Jehovah's people, this wonderful heritage we all have.

00:33:34.710 --> 00:33:48.710
To understand more, this wonderful deep Bible gems, Bible lessons for my life, and to feel more Jehovah's love and love of brothers and sisters, especially here.

00:33:48.710 --> 00:33:56.710
You know, my family, they had just a few magazines, a few books, and song books.

00:33:56.710 --> 00:34:01.710
But it was enough for them to build a strong face in Jehovah.

00:34:01.710 --> 00:34:14.710
So, in the new world, I want to see all of my big, big family, and I want to share with them this wonderful gems I learned here on Gilead while they were sleeping.

00:34:14.710 --> 00:34:21.710
And I want to say them, thank you for setting such a good example of face for me.

00:34:21.710 --> 00:34:28.710
Well, Angel, you have certainly touched our hearts by means of that beautiful story.

00:34:28.710 --> 00:34:35.710
Thank you for sharing your family legacy with all of us. We really appreciated that.

00:34:35.710 --> 00:34:38.019
Thank you.

